Methods  of document object:
•	Getting an element by id 
•	Getting an element by class name: Returns all the elements having the same class name, returns in the form of html collections object
An html collection is array like list of HTML element length property provides the size of the collection   
let x= document.getElementsByClassName('a')
        for(let i=0; i<x.length;i++){
            console.log(x[i])
        }
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         


•	Getting an element by tag name
•	let x=document.getElementsByTagName('hi')
•	        console.log(x)
•	
•	        for(let i=0; i<x.length;i++){
•	            console.log(x[i])
•	        }

•	Getting an element by query selector

	Query selector : used to select HTML elements by its class name ,tag name; it selects only the first element
Example
  let x=document.querySelector('hi')
        console.log(x)



	Query selector all: used to select HTML elements by its class name ,tag name;



Example:
let x=document.querySelectorAll('hi')
        console.log(x)
manipulate elements:
 to create a HTML element:
---- to createElement()
---- document>createElement()
---- the method takes an HTML element tag name as string Parameter
Example:
let t=document.createElement('h2')
        t.className='tt'
        t.textContent="iam in hyd"
        console.log(t)
